```java
if (namespaceURI != null && nodeNS != null) {
    // Both have namespaces - compare namespace URIs only
    return equalStrings(namespaceURI, nodeNS);
}
else if (namespaceURI == null && nodeNS == null) {
    // Both have no namespace - compare prefixes 
    return equalStrings(testPrefix, getPrefix(node));
}
else {
    // One has namespace, other doesn't - no match
    return false;
}
```

This ensures that:
1. If both test and node have namespaces, only compare namespace URIs (ignoring prefixes)
2. If both test and node have no namespace, compare prefixes
3. If one has a namespace and the other doesn't, they should not match

